SUMMARY:Coyote Wall Loop via Labyrinth and Little Maui 
DESCRIPTION:The Portland Hiking Meetup Group\nDistance: \\~7.5 miles\nElevation Gain: \\~1600 feet\nDifficulty: Moderate\nTotal Hiking Time: \\~ 5 hours\nTravel: 1.5 hours each way from carpool point\nPermits: None\nCarpool: $15\, including bridge toll\n\nJoin us for one of my favorite Gorge hikes. Wildflowers have started appearing in the eastern Gorge area.\n\nThere are many ways to get up to the Coyote Wall\, and this route has a lake at the base\, amazing wildflowers\, a super secret cave\, a maze of basalt curiosities\, an oak woodland\, (easy) stream crossings\, numerous viewpoints of the Columbia River and Gorge\, and several waterfalls along the way.\n\nOur start is at the Syncline Trailhead East near Rowland Lake at Highway 14 and Old Highway 8 in White Salmon\, WA (not the Labyrinth Trailhead which is at Courtney Road). Links: [apple maps](https://maps.apple.com/?ll=45.705407\,-121.382788&q=Dropped%20Pin&_ext=EiYpptE4RrPZRkAxZgg+fudYXsA5JKdeotnaRkBBKFAzvRRYXsBQBA%3D%3D&t=m)\, [google maps](https://goo.gl/maps/ggfXwo3cWMYX4Dny6).\n\nWTA hike description: [The Labyrinth](https://www.wta.org/go-hiking/hikes/catherine-creek-the-labyrinth)\n\nCARPOOLING: We will organize carpooling at Gateway Transit Center parking garage at 7:45 am. Make sure to arrive on time or preferably few minutes earlier for prompt departure. Or you can meet us at trailhead at 9:15 am. If carpooling\, suggested payment of $15 to the driver to share the cost of gas\, car\, tool.\n\n* Sturdy water proof hiking boots/shoes\n* Lunch\, snacks\, water\n* 3-4 Clothing layers\, rain jacket\n* Backpack\, cover for backpack\n* Trekking poles recommended\n\nMy hiking style is to stop frequently by creeks\, wild-flower meadows\, geological marvels and conversation\, and not to rush through it. We stay together as a group. I reserve the right to remove anyone from the hike based on their fitness level\, attendance record\, incomplete profile\, or if you were not a good fit with my group based on your presence on my previous hike.\n\n* If you are on the going list\, and decide to cancel\, please change your RSVP to "No" asap. Canceling after 8 pm on the day before the hike will result in a no-show on your record.\n\nDisclaimer: Hike leaders are volunteers to do their best to make it an enjoyable experience for everyone\, but assume no liability for any loss\, damage\, injury\, emergency evacuation\, during the event or getting to or back from an event. Each member is required to read and approve the waiver when agreeing to become a member\, and is completely responsible for their own safety and well-being.\nLink to liability waiver below:\n[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1e9K3R6KkepF8BFHmLdcTnPzou42_x2DEu38XqzlGfJ8/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1e9K3R6KkepF8BFHmLdcTnPzou42_x2DEu38XqzlGfJ8/edit?usp=sharing)
